<!-- Callout — spec card render
     Source spec: ds-architect-agent/children/components/feedback.md#callout -->
<div class="dst-component-card">
  <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Callout</h3>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 font-mono">3 variants · 1 size · 1 state</p>
  </div>
  <p class="dst-component-intro">In-content highlight box. Used inside docs / articles to call out a tip, note, or warning. Distinct from alert (alert is dismissible system feedback; callout is editorial emphasis).</p>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">Variants</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-variant">tip</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-variant">note</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-variant">warning</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">Sizes</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-size">md · 16px padding</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">States</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-state">idle</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-note"><strong>Structure:</strong> icon + label (e.g., "Tip") | body (markdown supported) | (optional) link. <strong>Placement:</strong> inline within long-form content. Never use as system feedback — that's <code>alert</code>.</div>
</div>
